fields.descriptive_line: Knitting patterns published by various manufacturers
fields.physical_description:
[Knitting pattern] For a child
V-necked single-breasted cardigan with wrist-length sleeves, patch pockets, and button-through fastening, worked in stocking-stitch with moss-stitch edgings, and vertical garter-stitch lines at front.

Playsuit, worked in stocking-stitch with garter-stitch edgings, and consisting of: top with turn-down collar, single-breasted button-through fastening, short sleeves, and honeycomb smocking at chest; shorts with button-through fastening to top at waist.
[Crochet pattern] Knitting pattern for garments for children aged 1-2 years and 2-3 years:
1. Pixie hood with pointed crown, worked in stocking-stitch with a ribbed border.
2. Rib-stitch scarf with fringed ends.
3. Stocking-stitch mittens with ribbed cuffs.
4. Socks worked in stocking-stitch without heel 	shapings.
fields.title: Cardigan and Playsuit; Toddlers' Accessories
fields.marks:
[Knitting pattern] 6-14 months
[Knitting pattern] 3d  original price (3 pence in pre-decimal coinage)
fields.public_access_description: Knitting clothing is creative, but also has the potential to be thrifty.  If necessary, a garment can be unravelled and knitted up again in a different size, with a contrasting welt and cuffs of some other yarn, or in stripes using up yarn from several old garments.  Because the knitted up yarn has a structure that is capable of stretching, it also gives a certain amount of elasticity to accommodate a child's growth.
